repository.corpname: Yale University. Department of Manuscripts and Archives

did.abstract: The records consist of administrative files, correspondence, catalogs, minutes, graduate student files, curricula, and printed material documenting the activities and operations of the Yale Department of Education, which no longer exists as a separate academic unit. Included are materials concerning the Summer Seminar in Education (formerly called the Education Conference), and the Yale-Fairfield Study of Elementary Teaching.

odd.head: General note
odd.p: Forms part of Yale Record Group 14-B (YRG 14-B), Records of academic departments and programs of the Yale Faculty of Arts and Sciences.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Access to the records is partially restricted. See Collection Contents for details.
